---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
    body-class="flex flex-col min-h-screen bg-white text-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200"
    ,
    header-navbar-class="sticky top-0 z-20 w-full flex-none"
>
    <section class="space-y-4">
        <div
            class="mx-auto items-center bg-linear-to-r from-blue-500 to-purple-600 pt-48 pb-40 text-center"
        >
            <h1
                class="text-center text-4xl font-semibold tracking-wide text-white uppercase md:text-6xl"
            >
                Privacy Policy
            </h1>
        </div>
        <div
            class="mx-auto flex max-w-(--breakpoint-xl) flex-wrap gap-2 pl-4 text-sm text-gray-400 [&>span:not(:last-child)]:after:mx-2 [&>span:not(:last-child)]:after:content-['|']"
        >
            <span>Updated: March 16, 2026</span>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- class="policy mx-auto flex max-w-(--breakpoint-xl) flex-1 flex-col justify-center space-y-8 px-4 py-4 md:space-y-12 lg:py-8" -->
    <main class="policy prose-wide mx-auto px-4 dark:prose-invert">
        <p>
            This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected through this website, how
            it is used, and how it is protected. By using this website or submitting a message
            through the contact form, you acknowledge the practices described in this policy.
        </p>

        <section>
            <h2>Information Collected</h2>
            <p>
                This website collects very limited personally identifiable information, which may
                include:
                <ul>
                    <li>Name</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>Message content</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                This information is voluntarily provided by you when you submit the contact form. No
                other personal information is intentionally collected.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Purpose of Data Collection</h2>
            <p>
                The information you provide through the contact form is used solely for the purpose
                of responding to your message and communicating with you regarding your inquiry.
                Additionally, technical measures, including Google reCAPTCHA, are used to protect
                the website from spam and automated abuse. Your information will not be used for
                marketing purposes, shared with third parties for advertising, or sold.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How the Information Is Processed</h2>
            <p>
                Contact form submissions are processed using Netlify Forms, a service provided by
                <span class="font-semibold text-heading underline decoration-brand"
                    >Netlify, Inc</span
                >. When you submit the form, the information you provide is securely transmitted and
                stored by Netlify in order to deliver the message. You can learn more about
                Netlify’s privacy practices here: <a
                    href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/"
                    class="text-fg-brand hover:underline">https://www.netlify.com/privacy</a
                >
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
                Personal information submitted through the contact form is retained only for as long
                as necessary to respond to your inquiry and maintain relevant correspondence.
                Information may be deleted periodically when it is no longer required.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Data Security</h2>
            <p>
                Reasonable measures are taken to protect submitted information. The website uses
                secure HTTPS connections, and form submissions are processed through Netlify’s
                infrastructure. However, no method of transmission over the internet can be
                guaranteed to be completely secure.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Rights of Data Subjects</h2>
            <p>
                In accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) applicable within
                the European Economic Area (EEA), individuals whose personal data is processed (data
                subjects) may have certain rights regarding their personal information. Depending on
                your location and applicable laws, you may have the right to:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Request <span class="font-semibold text-heading underline decoration-brand"
                            >access</span
                        > to the personal information you have provided.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Request <span class="font-semibold text-heading underline decoration-brand"
                            >correction</span
                        > of inaccurate or incomplete information.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Request <span class="font-semibold text-heading underline decoration-brand"
                            >deletion</span
                        > of your personal information when it is no longer necessary for the purposes
                        for which it was collected.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                If you wish to exercise any of these rights, you may contact the website owner using
                the contact form available on this website. Requests will be handled in accordance
                with applicable data protection regulations.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>This website uses third-party services to support its functionality.</p>
            <h3>Netlify</h3>
            <p>
                Contact form submissions are processed through Netlify, which acts as a data
                processor for the purpose of handling and delivering form submissions.
            </p>
            <h3>Google reCAPTCHA</h3>
            <p>
                This website uses Google reCAPTCHA to protect forms from spam and abuse. reCAPTCHA
                analyzes user interactions and device information to determine whether a request is
                made by a human. This process may involve the collection of data such as IP address,
                browser and device information, and user interaction patterns. The use of reCAPTCHA
                is subject to the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a
                        href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                        class="text-fg-brand hover:underline">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a
                    >
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a
                        href="https://policies.google.com/terms"
                        class="text-fg-brand hover:underline">https://policies.google.com/terms</a
                    >
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect changes to the
                website or legal requirements. Updates will be published on this page with the
                revised date.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>
                If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or the handling of your
                data, you may get in touch through the contact form available on this website.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
